          <tr><td>Tool doesn&rsquo;t actuate (right headlight flashes continuously)</td><td>Jammed fastener</td><td>Remove battery, clear the jam (push the driver blade back with the stall release lever), reinsert battery</td></tr>
          <tr><td rowspan="2">Tool doesn&rsquo;t actuate (headlights on, motor doesn&rsquo;t run)</td><td>Motor stopped after 4 seconds (normal)</td><td>Release the trigger or contact trip and re‑depress</td></tr>
          <tr><td>In sequential mode, only the trigger is being pulled</td><td>Depress the contact trip too, or change mode</td></tr>
          <tr><td rowspan="3">Tool operates but doesn&rsquo;t drive the fastener fully</td><td>Depth set too shallow</td><td>Rotate the depth wheel to a deeper setting</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Low charge or damaged battery</td><td>Charge or replace the battery</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Tool not firmly applied to the workpiece</td><td>Press firmly against the work surface</td></tr>
          <tr><td rowspan="2">Tool operates but no fastener driven</td><td>No fasteners, or wrong size/angle</td><td>Load the correct recommended fasteners</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Debris in nosepiece or magazine</td><td>Clean the nosepiece and magazine</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Tool is locked out, no fastener driven</td><td>Dry‑fire lock out (low staples)</td><td>Load fasteners into the magazine</td></tr>
        </tbody>
